SIMPLE: anticlimax
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anticlimax
<hw>An`ti*cli"max</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld>
<def>A sentence in which the ideas fall, or become less important and
striking, at the close; -- the opposite of <xex>climax</xex>. It
produces a ridiculous effect.</def></p>

<note><p>Example:</p>

<p><q>Next comes Dalhousie, the great god of war,⟦br⟧
Lieutenant-colonel to the Earl of Mar.</q>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>
</note>

<p><ent>Anticlinal</ent>⟦br⟧
